title: Don't Build Multi-Agents
creator: cognition
synopsis: Walden Yan (Cognition/Devin) argues against multi-agent architectures via two principles: share full context traces (not just messages) and recognize that actions carry implicit decisions that conflict when parallelized. Recommends single-threaded linear agents with context compression for long tasks.

Covers the four quadrants (individual/collective x interior/exterior) and developmental stages (premodern, modern, postmodern, second-tier). Argues that genius thinking synthesizes multiple perspectives rather than locking into one dogmatic worldview.

title: How To Think Like A Strategic Genius 5D Thinking @Thedankoe
creator: Dan Koe (thedankoe)
synopsis: Dan Koe introduces a 5-dimensional thinking framework progressing from one-dimensional (tribal, reductionistic) to genius-level thought. Distinguishes horizontal knowing (domain expertise) from vertical understanding (cognitive operating system sophistication), arguing that the 'smart but dumb' phenomenon stems from being horizontally advanced but vertically stuck.

Enables a visual planning workflow where Claude generates diagrams, the user edits them visually, and Claude reads the changes ‚Äî creating a bidirectional visual feedback loop before writing implementation code.

title: The Future Of Work When Work Is Meaningless @Thedankoe
creator: DAN KOE (thedankoe)
topics: philosophy; career; content-creation; ai-engineering; opinion; framework
synopsis: Dan Koe explores what happens to creative work and meaning when AI automates most production. Traces the meaning crisis through societal evolution (premodern to metamodern), argues that meaning itself becomes the scarce good in a post-AGI economy, and proposes that human experience, struggle, and curiosity are the irreplaceable elements.

title: The Dopamine Trap Why You Cant Focus And The 8 Day Fix @Drdominicng
creator: Dr. Dominic Ng (DrDominicNg)
synopsis: Neuroscientist Dr. Dominic Ng explains how chronic overstimulation raises the dopamine baseline, making focused work feel like deprivation. Makes the case for polymathy as competitive advantage, identifying three traps multi-interested people face (framework problem, validation problem, quality gap) and proposing cross-domain synthesis as the key differentiator.

title: David Deutsch on AGI vs AI Distinction and Constructor Theory
creator: Strange Loop
synopsis: David Deutsch argues AGI is qualitatively different from current AI: it requires explanatory knowledge creation (Popperian conjecture and criticism), not pattern matching. title: Ethan Mollick on AI Jagged Frontier, Abundance Mindset, and Knowledge Collapse

synopsis: Ethan Mollick presents the jagged frontier concept: AI capability is fundamentally uneven across tasks, demanding organizational redesign rather than plug-in adoption. title: The End of AI - Complete Integration into Society

creator: NVIDIA

title: Macroscopic Quantum Tunneling to Quantum Computing
